# npm i dotenv 👉 Reminder to install dotenv package
# 👆
# npm → Node Package Manager (used to install packages)
# i → shortcut for install
# dotenv → a package to use environment variables
# What it does?
# It installs the dotenv package in your project so you can:
# a) Store important data (like DB URL, PORT, API keys) in a .env file
# b) Keep them secure and separate from code

# File name: .env
# This file is used to store secret / configuration values. 
# .env file is used to store environment variables like database URL and port for security and flexibility.